metadata.name: fiction | non-fiction #01
metadata.description:
Perceived reality is merely what is perceived through various organs. It is too arbitrary a non-fiction to be called reality.
Memories are filled with fictions that are falsified and compiled without our awareness. If there is an interchangeable symmetry between fiction and non-fiction, how do our images appear to us?
